No Diabetes UK group in your area? Why not think about starting a group?
Diabetes UK groups are at the heart of our mission to improve the lives of
people living with diabetes and to work towards a future without the
condition. If you decide to set up a Diabetes UK group, you will be joining a
network of nearly 400 groups, all run by volunteers, dedicated to improving
the lives of people with diabetes in their local area.
We have groups for adults with diabetes as well as groups for children and
Diabetes UK is committed to supporting its group network. Your regional or
national office are there to provide you with all the support you need to set
* a range of resources to support you to run your group 
* free safeguarding advice, training and criminal records checks.
We've also got more resources about starting up a local group.
Running a group can be hard work but it can also be a very rewarding
experience. You can focus on things that interest you – whether that's
fundraising, awareness-raising, campaigning or offering support. Some groups
are small and informal, some are large groups – and there's everything in
If you are interested in a setting up a group, please contact your local
